BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:Mkg73CcjYUj3vpC3thNaI
SUMMARY:LS 101: Basics of Live Sound
DTSTAMP:20260402T030257Z
DTSTART:20260521T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:Basics of Live Sound is a 2-hour introduction to live audio eng
	ineering and an orientation to Vera Project’s methods and equipment. Topic
	s covered include an introduction to microphones and mic placement\, signa
	l paths\, stands\, cables\, DI’s\, snake\, sub-snakes and etiquette for wo
	rking with bands. This class is designed for both the novices and experts 
	of all ages and will give an overview of signal flow and setting up small 
	PAs\, in addition to the basic requirements for being part of the Vera sou
	nd team at shows. Discover why the accommodating\, open minded “Vera Attit
	ude” of show production is appreciated worldwide!\n\nThis class is a prere
	quisite for advanced audio classes at Vera and Sound Runner shifts at Vera
	 Project show. Each Live Sound class unlocks new audio engineering volunte
	er shifts at Vera and eventually paid opportunities in and outside of the 
	venue. Become a volunteer at Vera to access other audio-related educationa
	l programs such as tours\, field trips\, and internships!\n\nhttps://link.
	dice.fm/Sc328380c016\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/Sc328380c016
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:sRsN-eNXQr-33ahCipBe1
SUMMARY:SP 101: Intro to VERA's Screen Print Studio
DTSTAMP:20260402T030257Z
DTSTART:20260521T010000Z
DESCRIPTION:This 2-hour\, comprehensive hands-on class teaches you all the 
	basics of screen printing at VERA’s screen printing studio: From hand-draw
	ing a stencil on transparency\, coating and burning a screen\, to pulling 
	your very first print! Get comfortable with Vera's shop layout\, equipment
	\, and culture. Learn techniques for creating screens\, terminology\, and 
	more to create 1-color projects in the print shop. Students will walk away
	 with the basic skills for screen printing 1-color paper prints\, and thei
	r own print of a special Vera design\, specific to the 101 class.\n\nThis 
	class is a prerequisite for 200-level classes at VERA\, as well as access 
	to Open Sessions to work on your own projects in VERA’s screen printing st
	udio.\n\nhttps://link.dice.fm/Seb8988e6788\n\nFrom The Vera Project
URL:https://link.dice.fm/Seb8988e6788
LOCATION:305 Harrison Street\, Seattle\, Washington 98109\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:vera-project
CATEGORIES:The Vera Project
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:4qqqMc-jyExZp_IEBK3JS
SUMMARY:The Insidious Trilogy: A THEATRICAL EVENT
DTSTAMP:20260402T030257Z
DTSTART:20260521T023000Z
DESCRIPTION:The centerpiece of the season will be the complete Insidious Tr
	ilogy . The Trilogy contemplates Jim Crow\, its history\, and its contempo
	rary manifestations\; it confronts America’s history of racial violence\, 
	systemic oppression\, and deliberate forgetting. It is not merely a series
	 of dances—it is a cultural intervention. The three works that make up the
	 trilogy are Strange Fruit\, Grief\, and Targeted. PERFORMANCE SCHEDULE Pl
	ease note that each performance day will present various works from the In
	sidious Trilogy. The complete Trilogy performs over five days in a 2-act o
	r 3-act rotating repertory format: Wed. May 20\, 2026: Strange Fruit\, Gri
	ef (two acts) Thur. May 21\, 2026: Strange Fruit\, Targeted (two acts) Fri
	. May 22\, 2026: Targeted\, Grief (two acts) Sat.\, May 23\, 2026: Strange
	 Fruit\, Grief\, and Targeted ( three acts\, with a dinner break ) Sun. Ma
	y 24\, 2026: Targeted\, Grief (two acts) GROUP & DISCOUNT TICKETS We belie
	ve dance should be accessible to all\, which is why we offer a variety of 
	discounts and flexible pricing options to all performances: $25 Tickets ar
	e available for groups of 5 or more adults. Enter the following code at ch
	eckout: GROUP Dance For All tickets are open to everyone at a discounted r
	ate of $10 per person. Pay-What-You-Can (PYWC) tickets ensure everyone can
	 experience our performances\, no matter their budget. These tickets are a
	vailable on a first-come\, first-served basis\, and there is no minimum am
	ount required to reserve a ticket. Please email admin@spectrumdance.org to
	 reserve a PWYC ticket.\n\nhttps://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pe.c/36947\n\nFr
	om Spectrum Dance Theater
URL:https://web.ovationtix.com/trs/pe.c/36947
LOCATION:Spectrum Dance Theater\, 800 Lake Washington Blvd E\, Seattle\, WA
	 98122
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:spectrum-dance
CATEGORIES:Spectrum Dance Theater
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
